Mylex Corp said it has received scheduledorders to resume shipments under an existing contract with oneof its major customers that it did not name.    In May it said it did not have product releases from thatcustomer.    Mylex also said it has introduced an International BusinessMachines Corp &lt;IBM> personal computer compatible system boardusing Intel Corp's &lt;INTC> 80386 microprocessor called the Mylex386-A motherboard.  It said standard configuration includes oneor four megabytes of onboard 32-bit random access memory and 64kilobytes of cache memory.    Mylex said it will market the product directly and throughdistributors to original equipment manufacturers, value-addedresellers and system integrators, with shipments to start inmid-April. Reuter&#3;